comments: Burks (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position on Lowry (TOR) and Noel (NYK) makes foot to foot contact with Lowry that causes him to trip.  The contact by Noel is illegal, but the foul is whistled on Burks.
Boucher (TOR) legally contests and cleanly blocks Burks' (NYK) jump shot attempt.
Siakam (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NYK) during the post up and Lowry (TOR) makes clean ball contact to temporarily dislodge the ball.
After recovering the loose ball, Randle (NYK) fumbles the ball and is allowed to legally dribble again upon regaining full control of the ball.
Lowry (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position on Randle (NYK) during the drive and cleanly dislodges the ball.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor is overturned and the Raptors are awarded possession.
Burks (NYK) and Siakam (TOR) engage and disengage off-ball and the contact is marginal.
Randle (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Lowry (TOR) and Lowry inadvertently steps on Noel's (NYK) foot after his gather.
Noel (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Trent Jr.'s (TOR) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Randle (NYK) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Siakam (TOR).
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of goaltending by Noel (NYK) is confirmed.
After cleanly intercepting the pass, Lowry (TOR) takes a legal two steps before starting his dribble.
A double dribble is correctly called when Siakam (TOR) brings two hands to the ball to end his dribble and then starts dribbling again.
Randle (NYK) fumbles the inbounds pass and maintains his pivot foot once he gains full control of the ball.
Siakam (TOR) commits a take foul on Randle (NYK).
Boucher (TOR) establishes himself in a screening position in Bullock's (NYK) path and absorbs the contact as Bullock engages on the screen.
Siakam (TOR) commits a take foul on Randle (NYK).
Randle (NYK) avoids making any contact with Boucher (TOR) as Boucher jumps for the inbounds pass and loses his balance when returning to the ground.
